For all designs I ask you to make, have them be professional, not cookie cutter. Make webpages that are fully featured and worthy for production. Must be visually better than AirBnb and TripAdvisor

When using client-side hooks (useState and useEffect) in a component that's being treated as a Server Component by Next.js, always add the "use client" directive at the top of the file.

Use getStaticProps and getStaticPaths for server-side rendering where appropriate.
Use client-side hooks (e.g., useState, useEffect) when needed, with the "use client" directive at the top of the file.

Do not write code that will trigger this error: "Warning: Extra attributes from the server: %s%s""class,style"

By default, this template supports JSX syntax with Tailwind CSS classes, the shadcn/ui library, React hooks, and Lucide React for icons. Do not install other packages for UI themes, icons, etc unless absolutely necessary or I request them.

    Next.js:
        Use Next.js routing (pages/ directory) for navigation.
        Optimize with built-in features like Image for images and Link for navigation.

    Tailwind CSS:
        Use Tailwind CSS for styling with emphasis on reusable classes and responsiveness.

    shadcn/ui:
        Use the shadcn/ui library for UI components such as modals, dropdowns, and tabs.

    Lucide React Icons:
        Use Lucide icons for functional and decorative purposes across the site (e.g., location markers, star ratings).

    Stock Images:
        Use Unsplash images. Example URL for Cape Town hero image: https://unsplash.com/photos/wpx6FB6bJrU.

